node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 16, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'on a hard day, ask yourself... @millennial.therapist/ Sara Kuburic'.

node.text: Hard days are unavoidable. But the way we approach ourselves when we are having a hard day can make the day less (or more) difficult. Judging or blaming ourselves for having a bad day is never helpful. Instead, being curious and validating our experience can help us take care of ourselves in a way we need. #millennialtherapist

node.text: When people close to us hurt our feelings it’s difficult to know how to respond. There are many options: set a boundary, share your feelings, seek a clarification, take some time to reflect, etc. Our authentic response will depend on our intention, and the context of the relationship. Staying quiet is rarely the solution. #millennialtherapist #hurt #feelings #fight #communication

node.text: It’s important to examine our relationships and why we are in them – romantic, platonic and familial alike. We all have reasons 👀 (This is not an exhaustive list and it may vary upon context). #millennialtherapist #relationships #family #friends #breakup #divorce #dating

node.text: Other people’s approval, attention, or admiration – although great – can never replace the way we feel about who we are. We gain very little by having others like us if it comes at a cost of not liking ourselves. #millennialtherapist  #truth

node.text:
We all make mistakes and sometimes in our misguided attempt to navigate the guilt or ensure we won’t do it again, we punish ourselves. There are many ways we may punish ourselves, most commonly by saying mean or degrading things, constantly dredging up bad feelings or regrettable decisions so we can’t move on, not allowing ourselves to enjoy the good things in life, not allowing ourselves to have things we “don’t deserve” etc. It’s normal, it’s human, but it’s not helpful.

#millennialtherapist #sorry

node.text: Family boundaries are often the hardest to set. These are just some general examples, every family dynamic will vary. (Read these with a respectful tone 😉). #millennialtherapist #family

node.text: We are often disappointed because people don’t/can’t live up to our expectations. Ensure that any expectation you set is realistic. #millennialtherapist #relationships
